\"3264\"]<a href=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_185053.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-195 size-full\" src=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_185053.jpg\" alt=\"Socket to remove thermostat housing bolt\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" \/><\/a> Here's the socket I used to remove the bolts.[\/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_197\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"3264\"]<a href=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_190019.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-197 size-full\" src=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_190019.jpg\" alt=\"Engine coolant thermostat removed\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" \/><\/a> Engine coolant thermostat removed.[\/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_198\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"3264\"]<a href=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_191311.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-198 size-full\" src=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_191311.jpg\" alt=\"New engine coolant thermostat in place\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" \/><\/a> New engine coolant thermostat in place.[\/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Reattach hose and replace coolant<\/strong><\/section><section>Put the hose back on where it was. Screw your drain plug back in. Replace coolant in the reservoir until you get to the line. Start the car and let it warm up. After the car has warmed up, shut it off, let it cool down and add more coolant until it gets to the line. Check the sensor and make sure it isn't leaking. You're done!<\/section><section><a href=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_191938.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-199 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/andrewdelosreyes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/04\/20150323_191938-e1428541573314-1024x931.jpg\" alt=\"Coolant reservoir\" width=\"625\" height=\"568\" \/><\/a><\/section>


